{
  "ticker": "STEX",
  "cik": "1530766",
  "name": "Streamex Corp.",
  "description": "Streamex Corp., a medical device technology company, provides advanced digital signal processing solutions for electrophysiology in the United States. The company offers the PURE EP platform, which delivers cardiac signal data to electrophysiologists during ablation procedures for the treatment of cardiovascular arrhythmias. It also develops and operates the Streamex Exchange platform, a blockchain-based platform that facilitates the tokenization and exchange of real-world assets for the tokenized gold market. In addition, the company offers software support, maintenance, and upgrade services. The company was formerly known as BioSig Technologies, Inc. and changed its name to Streamex Corp. in September 2025. Streamex Corp. was incorporated in 2009 and is headquartered in Winter Park, Florida.",
